The paper deals with the representation of agent dynamics and interactions, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Algorithmic Information Theory (AIT) to analyze the complexity of player interactions suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the compatibility of the proposed construction with Universal Artificial Intelligence, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of set intersections to represent agent dynamics suggests a connection to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
